step.reason:
\text{Only matrices having the {\bf same order} i.e.}\\
\text{equal no. of rows (m) and equal no. of}\\
\text{columns (n) can be added.}

A_{m \times n} + B_{m \times n} = S_{m \times n}\\
\text{Thus, resultant matrix S has m rows and}\\
\text{n columns.}

A_{m \times n} + B_{m \times n} = S_{m \times n} = [s_{ij}]_{m \times n}\\
\text{where } s_{ij} = a_{ij} + b_{ij} \, (\forall \text{ possible ij values}).\\
\text{Therefore, corresponding elements are added.}
